<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1909-12-29T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1909-12-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="428" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d428">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 6369/539.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Chargé <persName type="from">Bailey</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1909-12-29"><hi rend="italic">December 29,
                                    1909</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Mr. Bailey reports the arrival of Zelaya and says about 300 Central
                            Americans and Mexican private citizens tendered him an enthusiastic
                            reception at the train.</p>
                        <p rend="center">(To be continued in <ref target="frus1910">Foreign
                                Relations, 1910</ref>.)</p>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>